post_text: Good Afternoon Cardinal Families. I am pleased to share that Felicity Schools has been awarded a Coronavirus Relief Funds – Broadband Ohio Connectivity Grant in the sum of $151,446.00. This grant money is earmarked to provide and/or improve high speed internet access to the families of the district. The district will be purchasing high speed internet equipped iPads, hot spots, and will be expanding the school WiFi outside of the building. Later this afternoon I will be emailing a survey to parents and also posting a link to the survey on the district website. It is extremely important that each family fill out and submit the survey. The district will use the information gathered to determine how to best deploy the new technology. I realize we gathered similar information last spring. However, we want to make sure our information is current and accurate.

The district will use the information gathered to determine how to best deploy the new technology. I realize we gathered similar information last spring. post_text:
Good Afternoon Cardinal Families.

I would like to share with you that Felicity Schools has been contacted by the Clermont County Public Health Department confirming positive test results for COVID 19 within the Felicity-Franklin Schools. Please understand that due to HIPA guidelines I am unable to share any further details.

CCPH will take the lead in any follow-up investigation as it relates to "close contacts/contact tracing" and will notify individuals IF deemed necessary. Felicity Schools will not contact individuals or families regarding any CCPH investigations.

I want to assure you that, in consultation with the Clermont County Public Health, we are continuing to follow state and local protocols to provide the safest environment possible for our students and staff.

Thank you

Dave Gibson
text:
Good Afternoon Cardinal Families.

I would like to share with you that Felicity Schools has been contacted by the Clermont County Public Health Department confirming positive test results for COVID 19 within the Felicity-Franklin Schools. Please understand that due to HIPA guidelines I am unable to share any further details.

CCPH will take the lead in any follow-up investigation as it relates to "close contacts/contact tracing" and will notify individuals IF deemed necessary. Felicity Schools will not contact individuals or families regarding any CCPH investigations.

I want to assure you that, in consultation with the Clermont County Public Health, we are continuing to follow state and local protocols to provide the safest environment possible for our students and staff.

Thank you

Dave Gibson

In May, the district released a virtual graduation ceremony and established August 9th as a date for an in-person/public graduation ceremony. Unfortunately, due to the current concerns and restriction surrounding COVID 19, the district will not be able to have an in-person/public ceremony. Regrettably, the August 9 ceremony is canceled.
I want to thank all of our seniors for what they have done for and meant to Felicity Schools. I wish them all the very best of luck in their future endeavors.
Dave Gibson, Superintendent

Hello Again Cardinal Families,
I’m sure the Governor’s order regarding mask requirements has added to your questions about the Return to School Plan.
I shared with you that the plan was subject to change and there were additional details to be worked out. I also stated that I wanted parents to have information so they could decide how they wanted their student(s) educated this fall.
I am working on a FAQ document with the goal of releasing it next week. Please know that even after its initial release, the FAQ document will be updated on a regular basis.
I understand that many questions still exist. I assure you that I am working to get you as many answers as possible as quickly as possible.
Thank you
Dave Gibson

Hello Cardinal Families,
Below is the link to the Felicity Schools Return to School Plan.

www.felicityschools.org/news

Please realize that this plan is based on today’s information and is subject to change. It is also important to note that there are still many details to be worked out regarding the day to day operations. We are releasing the plan as it exists today in hopes that you as parents/guardians have the details needed to begin your decision making process to determine if you are sending your student(s) to school this August.
I will be releasing updated information and day to day operation details over the next several weeks. Please check your email and our communications platforms on a regular basis.
Felicity Schools has been and continues to be committed to providing your students with the highest quality education in a safe environment.
Thank you in advance for your support and patience.
Sincerely,
Dave Gibson, Superintendent

To all of our kindergarten families and those who love and support them!

Please grab a tissue and click on the link to view the virtual graduation for our kindergarten class of 2020.
http://bit.ly/ffel2020k

Next week, each kindergarten family will receive a CD of the graduation and each kindergarten graduate will receive a t-shirt purchased by our PTO to commemorate this special event. To honor them, our goal is to have a parade through the hallway, with our kindergarten graduates wearing their cap and t-shirt, when we are able to return to the school building in the fall. A special thanks to the parents, kindergarten teachers and Michael Roush for all of the contributions and work on the graduation video. CONGRATULATIONS TO THE KINDERGARTEN CLASS OF 2020! WE ARE SO PROUD OF YOU!!!

post_text:
Seniors and Senior Families!

We will be making deliveries this coming Monday, June 1, from 5-8pm.

We will be bringing your Diplomas, Senior Yard Signs, and Photos from Graduation to you!

We would like to snap a quick picture of you with your sign and diploma for our social media.

Seniors to avoid delays in receiving your diploma, please settle any debts owed. Senior parents were sent email invoices for debts through our “Cube” account for easy payment.

Please email me at walkerb@felicityohioschools.org if you will not be home on Monday, June 1 from 5-8pm so that other arrangements can be made.

Have a great day!
Principal Walker

Congrats to all the officer candidates! 💛💙

post_text:
Good Afternoon.

A few moments ago Governor DeWine announced that Ohio students will not return to school buildings for the remainder of this academic school year. He stated that remote learning will continue. He also shared that no decision has been made regarding our return to school in the fall.

With this announcement comes many questions. Over the next days and weeks the Board of Education and administration will be sharing with you how Felicity Schools will finish this school year. Questions regarding grades, credits, promotion/retention, graduation and summer learning opportunities will be answered.

Thank you

Dave Gibson

post_text: Happy National Census Day! If you haven't already been counted, please take a moment to go to www.census.ohio.gov to be counted. You can also call 844-330-2020. As Treasurer/CFO of Felicity schools, I can't stress enough how important it is to be counted. The distribution of more than $675 billion in federal funds, grants, and support to states, counties and communities are based on census data. That is money spent on schools, hospitals, roads, public works and other vital programs. #BECOUNTEDOHIO

post_text:
Good afternoon Felicity-Franklin Families,

Please be advised we are happy to announce FFLSD is collaborating with the United Methodist Church & the Church of Christ to provide ANY child 1-18 years of age with lunch & breakfast meals.

Beginning today, on Tuesdays & Thursdays pickup is located outside the United Methodist Church (West Street near parking lot) from 2-3pm.

Beginning tomorrow, on Wednesdays, meals will be available for pickup at South Park from 11-1pm.

Again, this is open to ALL children 1-18 years of age. Children do not need to be on free & reduced lunch. Children do not need to be Felicity-Franklin students. We will provide meals for as many children as possible on a first come first serve basis.

When picking up please remember to follow all directions and maintain appropriate health & safety protocols while in line.

Please share this information with your neighbors that may be in need, perhaps this will help their student as we navigate these remote learning opportunities.

Families with school children currently without internet or WiFi, this may be helpful to gaining access to both at home. Contact, Spectrum at 844-488-8395. Charter Spectrum will offer free Spectrum broadband and Wi-Fi access for 60 days to households with K-12 and/or college students who do not already have a Spectrum broadband subscription at any service level up to 100 Mbps. To enroll call 1-844-488-8395. Installation fees will be waived for new student households.

post_text:
Dear Felicity-Franklin Families,

By now, most of you know of Governor DeWine’s announcement that schools in Ohio will be closed starting Monday, March 16 and reopen April 6. I am sure you have a lot of questions.

Our administration is working on a detailed plan for your students and will have those details regarding school work, grade cards etc. for you tomorrow.

In the short term, Felicity-Franklin schools will be on a two hour delay tomorrow, Friday, March 13. Staff will report at regular time.

Felicity Schools will be closed beginning Monday, March 16 and will reopen Monday, April 6.

We are using the two hour delay to allow teachers time to begin preparing learning materials for students to use during the three week closer.

Assuming your child is not ill, it is very important that your student(s) attends school tomorrow. Students will receive educational materials as well as important updates for you.

David R. Gibson, Superintendent
Felicity Franklin Local Schools
(513)876-2113

REMINDER - Don't forget, tomorrow, Tuesday, February 25th, ALL Junior and Sophomore students are to report at the normal time for the ACT, 7:15 - 7:30 am. We will be providing breakfast for FREE so that everyone gets their day started off right. Testing will begin promptly after arrival & breakfast.

Students are encouraged to bring their own snacks for break times during the day.

Senior and Freshman students are NOT to report to school on Tuesday, February 25th.

We anticipate all testing to be completed between ~7:30 am and Noon. Lunch will be served at Noon until 12:30 pm. Following lunch, all Sophomores and Juniors may be dismissed for the day. While there is no special transportation, any Sophomore or Junior who rides the bus or chooses to stay, is welcome. Students remaining will stay in a study hall session and/or receive intervention/support until the buses dismiss at 2:30 pm.

Have a great day!

post_text:
STATE CHAMPIONS!! Congratulations to the Advanced Parliamentary Procedure team for winning the state event today!! They have spent countless hours learning how to efficiently and properly conduct a business meeting as well as think on their feet and speak in public- all skills that will be very useful in their careers!

They will get to represent Ohio at the the 2020 National FFA Convention!

Team members include Audrey Pinger, Luke Jennings, Emily Hardewig, Alisha Boone, Carly McClure, Kyra Davidson, Emma Robertson, Landen Tull & Raven Schnarrenburg!

#agreatdaytobeacardinal

Good Morning Cardinal Families,

We are excited to share with you our first publication of the Cardinal Communication. Cardinal Communication is our new district newsletter. We hope you find it informative while enjoying a window into some of the things happening the first quarter of the 2019-2020 school year.

Please click on the link below to access the Communication.

http://www.felicityschools.org/o/felicity-franklin/browse/86718

If you have trouble accessing the Communication using the link, you can also access it through our website under the documents tab.

We hope you enjoy it!

Dave Gibson

post_text:
Attention elementary parents!!
By now, you should have seen this brochure come home letting you know you were eligible to receive a free Kinsa smart thermometer through October 15. Great news - Kinsa has extended that deadline until October 31!
19% of families have already signed up - join them! To sign up and order your thermometer, tap this link from your smartphone to download the Kinsa app and join our school group: https://get.kinsahealth.com/newUser
Cheers to a healthier flu season!
